Hi 👋I am Jen & I have not posted in a hot minute 😂😂- I am not gonna lie, I have struggled with social media in the aspect of "what am I using this for?" "What are my intentions?"...do I combine my personal life with my business? And if I do, how "raw" do I get? How can I use this platform for some good & not just pretty pics of jewelry and motivational quotes? 🤔 I know this word is overused & dare I say "trendy" , but what I have determined is the best answer is to be AUTHENTIC. To do what I feel without second guessing it. 🙌 going forward I might post pics of my dogs, my husband, the boutiques, colorado landscapes, selfies with my loved ones, a good hair day, my latest handmade jewelry, a bad hair day, a peek into the struggle with my weight/food and how I am losing lbs, our latest project on our fixer upper home, things I am proud of, things I am embarrassed or quite frankly ashamed of ...because that is what makes this life a wild beautiful ride & we are all on it together. 🌎 ✌🏼I am not out for a bigger number of followers but rather  follower-friends that feel my vibe. I hope you love the jewelry I make, the clothing we offer and are able to visit my boutiques in Colorado but most importantly, I hope we get to know eachother- CONNECT and become better people because of it. 💁🏼 PS- this pic was taken a few days ago when I was taking advantage of a good hair day😂...showcasing my bar necklace with my favorite quote of all time "SheWhoDaresWins" 💁🏼#appropriate #HelloAgain #keepinItReal #shewhodareswins #shamelessselfie #authenticity #letsconnect #goodvibes #jewelrydesigner #introduction #reallife #WelcomeToMyNewInstagram #LoveHarper #LoveHarperBoutique #colorado

Put a #frog into a vessel fill with water and start heating the water.
As the #temperature of the water begins to rise, the frog adjust its body temperature accordingly.
The frog keeps adjusting its body temperature with the increasing temperature of the water. Just when the water is about to reach #boiling point, the frog cannot adjust anymore. At this point the frog decides to #jump out.
The frog tries to jump but it is unable to do so because it has lost all its #strength in #adjusting with the rising water temperature.
Very soon the frog #dies.
What #killed the frog?
Think about it!
I know many of us will say the boiling water. But the #truth about what killed the frog was its own inability to decide when to jump out.
We all need to adjust with people & situations, but we need to be sure when we need to adjust & when we need to move on. There are times when we need to face the situation and take #appropriate actions.
If we allow people to exploit us
#physically, #emotionally, #financially, #spiritually or #mentally they will continue to do so.
Let us decide when to jump!
Let's jump while we still have the strength.
